            <note type="editorial" place="middle" resp="#ht"><hi rend="underline">pass to p.5</hi></note>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02487.002_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">54 Manchester Road</name>
                    <name type="place">Bolton, England</name>
                    <date when="1891-06-17">June 17<hi rend="underline">th</hi> 1891</date>
                </dateline>
            </opener>
            <p>Just another word of loving greeting &amp; good cheer, wafted from 
                over sea to you my dear good old Friend &amp; to send you a message
                of love &amp; sympathy.</p>
            <p>I do hope you are keeping better now &amp; that by this time you are
                able to get out &amp; to enjoy the sunshine &amp; fresh air.</p>
            <p>I herewith send
                <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02487.003_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
                you a dozen more facsimiles of your letter.</p>
            <p>I am also sending—or have sent—copies to the following.
